<br>
It seems that revelations of family holding dark emotion, shame for me and great grief for you, plague the Harvest this past week. In a time where we should be rejoicing, you are healing from a love that can never be more than that of brother and sister, while I lose myself in violence to try to discover how weak my half-bred blood has left me.<br>
<br>
Selilya, we are truly siblings of spirit it seems, and you know I stand beside you as you walk this road.<br>
<br>
Subati, your courage and honor have been a binding force for the Harvest reborn, and I know that you too are healing from this brutal blow.<br>
<br>
And yet, the news is not all dire. I know that once the wounds of interrupted romance will heal in time, and each of you has found a member of a family that you never new existed. Your Houses now hold honor unimagined with your positions in the vanguard of Neriak's elite. Persevere, and you will both see that there is great richness, driven to your hand not by the goddess of love, but rather through the truth of Hate.<br>
<br>
I stand ready for you both, I stand ready for the Harvest. This news strengthens your Houses, and so strengthens the Harvest. In these things, you will find yourselves the stronger for it as well.<br>
<br>
Nospiratus K'Thalion<br>
Priest and Prophet of Innoruuk  <br>
